The paper deals with the P versus NP problem, which is a fundamental problem in computational complexity theory. The use of the relational model of E. F. Codd suggests a focus on databases and data structures, which are covered by cs.DB and cs.DS. The paper also involves the analysis of algorithms and their complexity, which falls under cs.CC. The use of shared trichoices and periodic machines suggests a connection to logic and automata theory, which are covered by cs.LO and cs.IT.
